  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\nCurrently rook operator is checking whether OSD tolerations allow OSDs to be running on every node, and if not, the OSDs will silently not be created on a node. Also it will REMOVE the OSDs from such a node on restart if it finds that tolerations are not matching. This causes 2 issues:\r\n1st issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/rook/rook/issues/2235\r\nhttps://github.com/rook/rook/issues/2112#issuecomment-434176672\r\n\r\nIt's really hard to debug what rook didn't like. If you just let ReplicaSets try to create the pods, it will be obvious why it's failing, and easy to fix the issue.\r\n\r\n2nd issue:\r\nIf I temporary cordon a node to prevent user jobs from running in it and operator restarts, it will delete all OSDs from the node. I'd definitely not want that.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\nN/A\r\n",
